00:37.465 --> 00:39.233
♪ Won't hurt anymore ♪

00:39.299 --> 00:40.434
Mmm‐mm‐mm.

00:40.500 --> 00:43.637
♪ It's an open smile ♪

00:43.703 --> 00:46.740
♪ On a friendly shore ♪

00:46.806 --> 00:48.641
♪ It's love ♪

00:48.707 --> 00:50.876
♪ Love love love ♪

00:50.943 --> 00:53.946
Oh, you're good!
You're gonna win!

00:54.012 --> 00:55.213
[ <i>Queen Latifah singing</i>
<i>"We Are Living Single"</i> ]

00:55.280 --> 00:58.983
♪ We are Living Single ♪

00:59.050 --> 01:01.625
♪ Ooo and in a '90s
kind of world ♪

01:01.692 --> 01:04.093
♪ I'm glad I got my girls ♪

01:04.160 --> 01:05.394
♪ Keep ya head up ♪
♪ What ♪

01:05.461 --> 01:06.963
♪ Keep ya head up ♪
♪ That's right ♪

01:07.030 --> 01:08.731
♪ Wheneva this life get tough
you gotta fight ♪

01:08.797 --> 01:10.866
♪ With my homegirl standin'
to my left and my right ♪

01:10.933 --> 01:12.634
♪ True blue
We tight like glue ♪

01:12.701 --> 01:15.770
♪ We are Living Single ♪
♪ Check check check it out ♪

01:15.837 --> 01:19.373
♪ What you want ♪
♪ No free position girl ♪

01:19.440 --> 01:21.442
♪ Ah‐h‐h ♪

01:25.645 --> 01:27.647
[flute music]

01:33.252 --> 01:35.554
So tell them the big news,
Khadijah.

01:35.621 --> 01:37.288
There is no news.

01:37.355 --> 01:38.556
I wouldn't say being asked

01:38.623 --> 01:40.858
to be the subject
of an on‐air TV interview

01:40.925 --> 01:43.427
with an award‐winning journalist
at our house next week

01:43.494 --> 01:46.496
at 7 o'clock, is no news.

01:46.563 --> 01:49.566
They're never gonna believe it.
Tell 'em, tell 'em.

01:49.633 --> 01:53.336
It's a lil' puff piece for that
TV show, "Black Visionaries."

01:53.402 --> 01:54.803
‐ Ooh.
‐ Mmm.

01:54.870 --> 01:57.005
You know, they interview all
the prominent African‐Americans

01:57.072 --> 01:59.841
in the city.
Hmm, note to Sabrina.

01:59.907 --> 02:02.750
Expect a call
from "Black Visionaries."

02:02.817 --> 02:04.118
Note to Sabrina.

02:04.185 --> 02:08.221
There are several poisons that
can't be traced. Think about it!

02:08.288 --> 02:09.622
"Black Visionaries."

02:09.690 --> 02:15.194
That's that show that comes
on after my soap, "Latino Love."

02:15.260 --> 02:18.063
Man, I wish I hadn't
agreed to do it.

02:18.130 --> 02:20.299
I mean, I'm a behind‐the‐scenes
kind of person.

02:20.365 --> 02:23.768
The truth is Khadijah stinks
at public speaking.

02:23.835 --> 02:27.137
I got a little speech for you.

02:27.204 --> 02:29.807
Anyway, in junior high
she had to give this speech..

02:29.873 --> 02:32.875
...and so she got up, wobbling
in her first pair of heels

02:32.942 --> 02:36.245
and she said,
"Principal H‐H‐Hernandez

02:36.312 --> 02:38.614
faculty and fellow students."

02:38.680 --> 02:44.019
And then, the girl fell out
her shoes and off the stage.

02:44.085 --> 02:46.321
Khadijah, you know,
it might be good for Flavor.

02:46.387 --> 02:48.355
‐ You should do the interview.
‐ Yeah, he's right.

02:48.422 --> 02:50.724
You owe this
to your readers and to me

02:50.790 --> 02:53.960
your personal image consultant.

02:54.027 --> 02:55.695
Oh, hells no!

02:57.196 --> 03:00.232
If I'm not mistaken,
you talked me into those shoes

03:00.298 --> 03:02.240
and your grandmother
did not appreciate me

03:02.307 --> 03:04.776
messing up her party pumps.

03:04.842 --> 03:07.111
Alright, yes, yes, yes.
Very good! Very good!

03:07.178 --> 03:09.113
Alright. Ha ha.
How about that?

03:09.180 --> 03:10.514
Wasn't that
a wonderful version

03:10.581 --> 03:13.650
of whatever it was you were
playing? Yeah, very good.

03:13.717 --> 03:18.588
Now, let's have all of tonight's
contestants up here on stage

03:18.654 --> 03:22.557
so we can announce tonight's
talented winner. Alright, huh?

03:22.624 --> 03:25.994
They give prizes
for this poop?

03:26.060 --> 03:28.763
Max, your eloquence
really turns me on.

03:28.830 --> 03:30.398
[growls]

03:30.464 --> 03:32.466
Well, thank you,
Eartha Kitt.

03:36.469 --> 03:39.506
And tonight's winners are

03:39.572 --> 03:43.909
once again the ventriloquist
duo, Puddin' and Fudge.

03:43.975 --> 03:45.777
Ha‐ha!

03:45.844 --> 03:48.947
Can't they find anybody
in this place with some talent?

03:49.014 --> 03:53.150
Hell, you got Nat King Kyle
sitting right here.

03:53.217 --> 03:56.553
Come on, Overton.
That was only one review.

03:56.620 --> 04:00.697
That you had laminated, and is
now hanging in our bathroom.

04:02.331 --> 04:05.368
Kyle, why don't you sing next
week in the Open Mike contest?

04:05.434 --> 04:09.071
Come on, you could at least
beat Puddin', if not Fudge.

04:10.705 --> 04:12.707
Yeah. Who knows
where this could lead?

04:12.774 --> 04:16.810
I mean, Frank Sinatra's doing
duets with anybody these days.

04:16.877 --> 04:20.480
If you think it's so easy, why
don't you tell your jokes, huh?

04:20.546 --> 04:22.482
This contest
is for amateurs.

04:22.548 --> 04:25.384
See, I've been paid
for my comedic style.

04:25.450 --> 04:30.689
Ah‐ha! You dressed as a cordless
drill at a hardware convention.

04:30.755 --> 04:34.225
For which I was paid $50.

04:34.291 --> 04:37.661
But I'd be willing to overlook
my professional status

04:37.728 --> 04:39.930
if it'd get you back on stage.

04:39.997 --> 04:42.299
Hey Kyle, I've heard you sing.
You're good.

04:42.365 --> 04:44.601
You people don't understand.
There has to be passion.

04:44.667 --> 04:46.335
I sing from my heart.

04:46.402 --> 04:48.404
First prize, $300.

04:48.470 --> 04:51.306
♪ The Love Boat ♪

04:51.372 --> 04:52.674
[all laughing]

04:58.913 --> 05:01.821
Khadijah, it's time
for your make‐over.

05:01.888 --> 05:03.256
Oh, no, you don't.

05:03.323 --> 05:05.258
Take that camera
up to your bedroom

05:05.324 --> 05:08.061
and put it back on the ceiling
mount, where it belongs.

05:11.630 --> 05:14.499
Khadijah, someone has got to
help you with this TV interview

05:14.566 --> 05:16.601
and it ain't gonna be Synclaire.

05:16.668 --> 05:18.035
Look at her.

05:18.102 --> 05:20.971
Hey, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey, hey.

05:23.006 --> 05:25.341
Girl, relax.
It's just a tactic.

05:25.408 --> 05:28.611
But you could use a little
hot oil treatment.

05:28.678 --> 05:31.613
Now, as for you, honey,
you have a really terrifically

05:31.680 --> 05:33.715
cute face here in real life

05:33.782 --> 05:37.852
but television, is a merciless
distorter of the truth.

05:37.919 --> 05:39.187
She's right.

05:39.253 --> 05:40.554
Look at Ed Asner.

05:40.621 --> 05:42.590
You think his ears
are really that hairy?

05:42.656 --> 05:45.425
Come on, TV does that.

05:45.492 --> 05:47.560
Regine, go away.

05:47.627 --> 05:48.595
‐ Synclaire.
‐ Huh?

05:48.661 --> 05:49.962
Seek help.

05:51.463 --> 05:54.500
Okay, I will take
my little miracle kit

05:54.566 --> 05:56.568
and work my magic
on someone else

05:56.635 --> 05:59.070
because see dear,
it is very obvious to me

05:59.137 --> 06:01.812
that you do not want my help.

06:05.249 --> 06:06.583
Okay, Regine.

06:06.650 --> 06:11.420
What did you do to the camera
to make me look like Yoda?

06:11.487 --> 06:12.988
I pressed record.

06:13.055 --> 06:14.357
Deal with it.

06:17.192 --> 06:20.795
Do I sit like that?
All hunched over?

06:20.862 --> 06:23.865
Damn, my eyes looked crossed.

06:23.931 --> 06:26.700
Just the one eye.

06:26.767 --> 06:29.102
Dang, look at your years.

06:31.037 --> 06:32.138
[softly]
My God.

06:32.205 --> 06:34.874
[scatting]

06:38.543 --> 06:39.878
Hey, hey, hey.

06:39.944 --> 06:41.913
Man, I was workin'
on my microphone technique

06:41.980 --> 06:43.281
with that remote.

06:43.347 --> 06:45.316
Man, last time you sang
in this thing

06:45.383 --> 06:49.252
you ended up recording six hours
of Korean home shopping.

06:49.319 --> 06:52.289
Overton, it takes a lot
of planning and practice

06:52.355 --> 06:55.157
to achieve the level of
brilliance to which I aspire.

06:55.224 --> 06:57.359
At the cafe?

06:57.426 --> 07:00.228
When your competition
is Food Mart Freddie

07:00.295 --> 07:03.972
the belchin' bag boy,
you're going to shine.

07:04.039 --> 07:07.041
Man, so you been walking around
here tormenting your self today.

07:07.107 --> 07:10.144
Just sing the damn song,
and sing it like you mean it.

07:10.210 --> 07:12.946
And if you sing that song,
"She's Out Of My Life"

07:13.012 --> 07:15.014
don't try to choke up
at the end.

07:15.081 --> 07:17.683
Hell, everybody'll know
it's phony.

07:17.750 --> 07:20.619
[singing high‐pitched notes]

07:21.720 --> 07:22.787
[knocking on door]

07:22.855 --> 07:24.789
Come on! Fire!
Get out! Come on!

07:24.856 --> 07:27.058
Oh God, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

07:27.124 --> 07:30.094
Hey, I thought your smoke alarms
were going off.

07:30.161 --> 07:32.095
Max, I'm so glad you're here.

07:32.162 --> 07:34.965
You know, it will remind me
not to sing so flat.

07:37.767 --> 07:41.536
Well, I'd think lack of stamina
would be your main concern.

07:43.005 --> 07:44.706
[chuckling]

07:44.773 --> 07:47.008
You know, coming from a woman
whose musical taste

07:47.075 --> 07:50.911
go no further than
"Alvin And The Chipmunks"..

07:50.978 --> 07:52.913
...I really wouldn't expect
you to understand.

07:52.980 --> 07:55.248
You see, I throw myself
on to my craft.

07:55.315 --> 07:59.318
I embrace the song
like I embrace a woman.

07:59.385 --> 08:01.460
So that's what?
Once a year?

08:04.863 --> 08:07.565
But it's a tune
you will never forget.

08:07.632 --> 08:10.335
Now..

08:10.401 --> 08:12.637
...if this conversation is over

08:12.703 --> 08:16.640
allow me to show you
the way...out.

08:18.742 --> 08:22.178
They need to let me
fix our foreign aid program.

08:22.245 --> 08:24.747
Every time I'm watching the TV
I see American planes

08:24.813 --> 08:27.449
dropping big bag of wheat
in some foreign country.

08:27.515 --> 08:30.452
Then they gonna try to tell me
it cost $300 million.

08:30.518 --> 08:32.519
I'm thinking,
hey, for $300 million

08:32.586 --> 08:35.621
couldn't we at least
throw in some butter?

08:37.090 --> 08:40.994
Or maybe some bouillon
or some biscuits for sopping?

08:44.296 --> 08:45.597
Anyway, look here.

08:45.665 --> 08:47.599
I've been Overton Wakefield
Jones and remember.

08:47.666 --> 08:49.601
Hey, don't drink and drill.

08:49.668 --> 08:50.635
Goodnight.

08:54.872 --> 08:58.141
Hey, how about that?
Overton Wakefield Jones. Ha ha.

08:58.208 --> 09:01.218
Y'know, I didn't think he was
gonna be any good, but hey!

09:01.284 --> 09:04.220
He is funny, isn't he?
Ha ha ha.

09:04.286 --> 09:06.522
Kyle, if you suck
on that lemon much longer

09:06.588 --> 09:10.459
your gonna have to
propose to it.

09:10.526 --> 09:12.493
Look, a singer needs something
bitter and sour

09:12.560 --> 09:16.931
before he sings, right?
And since Max is not here..

09:16.997 --> 09:18.933
You're looking a little nervous
there, partner.

09:18.999 --> 09:21.301
Mmm, no. It's just
pre‐performance anxiety.

09:21.368 --> 09:23.302
I think I can handle this crowd.

09:23.369 --> 09:27.640
Whoo! That was scariest thing
I ever did in my life.

09:27.706 --> 09:29.975
I mean, when you're
Reba McIntyre, it's easy.

09:30.042 --> 09:32.377
In front of 50,000 people,
no problem.

09:32.444 --> 09:35.280
But here, where you can
see each and every face..

09:35.347 --> 09:37.281
Whoo!

09:37.348 --> 09:39.950
Good luck up there, dog.

09:40.017 --> 09:41.518
[drumroll]

09:41.585 --> 09:43.553
Alright, alright
and right on with the show.

09:43.620 --> 09:45.989
Now this next guy up
calls himself

09:46.056 --> 09:49.291
"The hardest working man
on Wall Street."

09:49.358 --> 09:51.193
Yeah, well,
what's that mean?

09:51.260 --> 09:56.698
Anyway, let's welcome the vocal
stylings of Kyle Barker, huh?

09:56.765 --> 09:58.432
[compere laughing]

10:01.342 --> 10:04.011
[fast scatting]

10:11.850 --> 10:16.521
♪ When I fall in love girl ♪

10:16.587 --> 10:19.524
♪ It's gonna be forever ♪

10:19.590 --> 10:21.025
♪ Yes ♪

10:21.091 --> 10:27.764
♪ Or I'll never fall in love ♪

10:27.831 --> 10:30.066
♪ I'm never gonna
fall in love babe ♪

10:30.133 --> 10:34.737
♪ In a restless
a restless world like this is ♪

10:34.803 --> 10:39.807
♪ Love is ended
before it's begun ♪

10:39.874 --> 10:44.911
♪ And too many
too many moonlight kisses ♪

10:44.978 --> 10:49.482
♪ Seem to cool
in the warmth of the sun ♪

10:49.549 --> 10:51.551
♪ Oh yes ♪

10:51.617 --> 10:56.555
♪ When I give my he‐he‐heart ♪

10:56.621 --> 11:00.632
♪ It's gonna be completely yes ♪

11:00.699 --> 11:03.734
♪ Or I'll ne‐nev.. ♪

11:10.207 --> 11:11.341
Wow!

11:11.408 --> 11:13.342
Check out loser Vandross. Pfft.

11:13.409 --> 11:15.077
[laughing]

11:19.748 --> 11:20.716
[Maxine laughing]

11:20.782 --> 11:21.983
Oh, come on, Kyle.

11:22.050 --> 11:24.552
Cheer up. It wasn't that big
a deal. For real.

11:24.619 --> 11:27.387
And‐and you didn't officially
come in last place.

11:27.454 --> 11:28.755
Yeah, yeah, yeah. True.

11:28.823 --> 11:31.291
When you ran out of there,
you were disqualified.

11:31.358 --> 11:32.959
[Maxine laughing]

11:33.026 --> 11:34.961
Don't dwell on that.

11:35.028 --> 11:37.263
You just put this whole
silly contest behind you.

11:37.330 --> 11:42.234
(Overton)
Hey, can somebody give me
a hand with this?

11:42.300 --> 11:44.802
Man, this is the biggest trophy
I ever seen.

11:44.869 --> 11:46.804
Now, Kyle, don't feel bad.

11:46.871 --> 11:49.006
You still have your dignity.

11:49.073 --> 11:51.107
Oh, no, you really don't,
do you?

11:51.174 --> 11:53.777
Oh‐h‐h! Ha‐ha‐ha!

11:53.844 --> 11:56.079
Why you gonna kick that man
when he's down?

11:56.146 --> 11:59.549
I'm sorry, but watching Kyle
humiliate himself in public..

11:59.615 --> 12:01.957
...it's got me kind of giddy.

12:12.299 --> 12:14.234
Oh, face it, man.

12:14.301 --> 12:16.636
Anybody who's ever
been on stage before

12:16.703 --> 12:19.238
has flopped
at one time or another.

12:19.305 --> 12:20.672
[grunts]

12:20.739 --> 12:22.374
Except for me,
of course.

12:22.441 --> 12:24.376
I'm batting a thousand
but then again

12:24.443 --> 12:28.213
that's an unfair comparison.

12:28.279 --> 12:30.247
Overton, man,
I completely lost it up there

12:30.315 --> 12:32.616
and why'd have
to be in front of Max?

12:32.683 --> 12:34.751
I'm never gonna hear
the end of this.

12:34.818 --> 12:37.320
You know, I think my avid
viewing of Ricki Lake

12:37.387 --> 12:40.189
is about to pay off.

12:40.256 --> 12:43.258
Kyle, I think Max is the reason
why you cracked on stage.

12:43.326 --> 12:46.061
Please, come on, man.
It'd take a lot more than her.

12:46.128 --> 12:48.630
As any Oprah fan
would tell you..

12:48.696 --> 12:51.165
...man, you in denial.
Let's face it.

12:51.232 --> 12:53.167
You and Max
have been intimate.

12:53.234 --> 12:57.003
You inoculated the cat. You took
Mr. Toad for the wild ride.

12:57.070 --> 13:00.213
‐ Y'all was doing the‐‐
‐ Ha‐ha! Okay!

13:02.315 --> 13:04.449
And yes, we did discuss
having a relationship

13:04.516 --> 13:05.818
but good sense prevailed

13:05.885 --> 13:09.621
allowing us to maintain
our mutual disgust.

13:09.688 --> 13:12.623
So, what I'm hearing here is..

13:12.690 --> 13:16.126
...you tried to get closer to
Max and she closed the doors.

13:16.193 --> 13:20.497
She cut you off,
she hung up the emotion phone.

13:20.563 --> 13:24.033
Or at least,
that's how Donahue would say it.

13:24.100 --> 13:27.869
Overton, man, I thought I had
put all this stuff behind me.

13:27.936 --> 13:29.605
Well, clearly you haven't.

13:29.671 --> 13:32.940
So what you got to do now
is get back on that stage

13:33.008 --> 13:35.242
in front of Max
and the other 50 people

13:35.309 --> 13:38.212
that laughed your ass up
out of there...and sing.

13:38.278 --> 13:39.579
I'll tell you another thing.

13:39.646 --> 13:42.381
I think the reason why Max
didn't hook up with you

13:42.449 --> 13:43.750
is 'cause she's scared.

13:43.817 --> 13:44.784
[snorts]

13:49.021 --> 13:50.555
You think so?

13:50.622 --> 13:53.358
Well, it's either that, or
she's just not attracted to you.

13:57.394 --> 13:59.363
Synclaire, would you mind
sitting in for Khadijah

13:59.430 --> 14:00.564
while we adjust lighting?

14:00.631 --> 14:03.439
Oh, I could never
take Khadijah's place.

14:03.506 --> 14:06.209
I'd love to!

14:06.276 --> 14:08.511
You know,
you're pretty photogenic.

14:10.913 --> 14:14.215
Damn! Look at all this
equipment. I'm not ready.

14:14.282 --> 14:16.951
Just remember
the regime routine.

14:17.018 --> 14:19.887
"Posture, poise,
smile, sincerity."

14:19.953 --> 14:24.424
Posture, poise,
smile, sincerity.

14:24.491 --> 14:26.993
Listen, if you find yourself
at a loss for words

14:27.059 --> 14:29.762
simply thank God and your family
for all the opportunities

14:29.829 --> 14:34.600
that you've been given,
and then the big smile.

14:34.666 --> 14:36.935
Khadijah, we're ready for you.
You look fantastic.

14:37.002 --> 14:38.303
Thank you!

14:43.974 --> 14:46.710
So, just pretend we're
two old friends chatting

14:46.776 --> 14:49.612
and I'll ask you
a few simple questions.

14:49.678 --> 14:52.014
Excuse me,
if you were old friends

14:52.080 --> 14:54.683
wouldn't you know the answers
to all the questions?

14:55.784 --> 14:57.085
[clears throat]

14:57.152 --> 15:00.221
So what is it like being
a young African‐American woman

15:00.287 --> 15:02.696
in charge of her own magazine?

15:02.763 --> 15:03.730
Nice.

15:07.701 --> 15:10.370
Um, it's very nice.

15:13.639 --> 15:15.807
Um, um, it's excellent.

15:15.875 --> 15:17.176
I‐I like it.

15:18.643 --> 15:20.579
Why don't I ask you
something easier?

15:20.645 --> 15:22.880
Now, for those viewers
who haven't been lucky enough

15:22.947 --> 15:26.116
to have read Flavor Magazine,
how would you describe it?

15:26.183 --> 15:28.785
Um, it's a magazine
that's called "Flavor"

15:28.852 --> 15:33.790
and‐and I publish it
and it's I‐I it's urban

15:33.856 --> 15:38.494
and is hip
and I is‐is, is um..

15:38.560 --> 15:40.528
I'd like to thank God
and my family

15:40.595 --> 15:42.730
for everything
they've done for me.

15:42.797 --> 15:45.032
Cut!
Cut!

15:45.099 --> 15:46.366
Cut!
Cut!

15:46.433 --> 15:48.435
Come on. Come here.

15:51.137 --> 15:54.740
Now, Khadijah, two important
things happened in here, honey.

15:54.807 --> 15:58.744
You're bombing and you're
making me look really bad.

